rComments: She was very helpful when she saw that I was struggling in this class. Definitely goes quickly in class because of how demanding it is, but is very accessible in office hours and gives good advice about how to approach mathematics as a whole. Even after her class I'm still in touch with her! She's very available to talk about future math prospects.

Camelia cares about the success of her students, however she ensures their success only during office hours. You need to make the effort to ask for help; Explanations are better 1:1, rather than in class. Team Homework is hard, and she is able to help- go to her for help. If you put in a lot of effort, you can pass this class.

She really cares about the students and if you are learning. I took proof-based Linear Algebra with her at the University of Michigan. It is a tough class, but she is really good in walking through the proofs and making sure everybody follows.
Camelia Karimianpour was the best Math professor I have ever taken. She explains everything really well and her notes are very organized. I would definitely recommend!
